ipping Services are likely failing at transaction or request logic points.\n   - Frontend service is experiencing an increased rate of server-side errors, indicating potential back-end failures or connectivity issues.\n\n### JSON Output\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\n    \"client_error_ratio\",\n    \"error_ratio\",\n    \"pod_cpu_usage\",\n    \"request\",\n    \"server_error_ratio\"\n  ],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"productcatalogservice-0\",\n      \"reason\": \"Increased client_error_ratio and error_ratio indicating request handling issues.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Metrics: client_error_ratio increased from 0.0 to 9.38, request decreased from 6765.0 to 132.0.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"cartservice-0\",\n      \"reason\": \"Sudden spikes in error_ratio pointing to possible transaction failures.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Metrics: error_ratio P99 value increased from 0.0 to 16.8.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"frontend-0\",\n      \"reason\": \"Server_error_ratio escalation suggests backend interaction issues.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Metrics: server_error_ratio increased from 0.0 to 27.66.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nThe data indicates widespread service disruptions with possible database or network dependencies. Further investigation into logs and system configuration during the fault period is recommended to pinpoint precise causes."}
